<div class="c510_4">
<div id="v510.4.1"><span class="G1161 s">And</span><span class="G846 s"> as they</span><span class="G2980 s"> spake</span><span class="G4314 s"> unto</span><span class="G2992 s"> the people</span><span class="G2409 s">, the priests</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G4755 s"> the captain</span><span class="G2411 s"> of the temple</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G4523 s"> the Sadducees</span><span class="G2186 s">, came upon</span><span class="G846 s"> them</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (captain: or, ruler)</span></div>
<div id="v510.4.2"><span class="G1278 s">Being grieved</span><span class="G1223 s"> that</span><span class="G846 s"> they</span><span class="G1321 s"> taught</span><span class="G2992 s"> the people</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G2605 s"> preached</span><span class="G1722 s"> through</span><span class="G2424 s"> Jesus</span><span class="G386 s"> the resurrection</span><span class="G1537 s"> from</span><span class="G3498 s"> the dead</span>.</div>
